column9: Pizza Salami with Swedish medwurst. Sorry but this pizza did not deserve to be called pizza with salami!
A great place for a lunch Kebab/Gyros, Kebarulle or Kebab plate, both are tasty. Pizzas are also good!
A place for a good, typical Swedish pizza. Nothing fantastic but really great and normal pricing. Seems like a favourite pizza place of many students who live closeby.

We ordered tuna pizza (without kapris, but garlic instead) and kebab "tellarik". Both arrived after very little waiting time. Taste was fresh and delicious as always. Free water, coffee, bread and cabage salad, one soft drink / light beer per dish included. About SEK 70.-...More
